{"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Class","title":"InvertedPendulum","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"externalID":"s:3Gym16InvertedPendulumC","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"Gym"}],"symbolKind":"class","role":"symbol"},"kind":"symbol","schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/init()"],"title":"Initializers"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/data","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/model"],"title":"Instance Properties"},{"title":"Default Implementations","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/Env-Implementations"],"generated":true}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"relationshipsSections":[{"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Env","doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/MuJoCoEnv"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"final"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"InvertedPendulum","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["Linux"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Description","level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Description"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This environment is the cartpole environment based on the work done by","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Barto, Sutton, and Anderson in ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"https:\/\/ieeexplore.ieee.org\/document\/6313077","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"just like in the classic environments but now powered by the Mujoco physics simulator -","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allowing for more complex experiments (such as varying the effects of gravity).","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"This environment involves a cart that can moved linearly, with a pole fixed on it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at one end and having another end free. The cart can be pushed left or right, and the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"goal is to balance the pole on the top of the cart by applying forces on the cart.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"type":"heading","anchor":"Action-Space","text":"Action Space"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The agent take a 1-element vector for actions."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The action space is a continuous "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"(action)"},{"type":"text","text":" in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"[-3, 3]"},{"type":"text","text":", where "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"action"},{"type":"text","text":" represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the numerical force applied to the cart (with magnitude representing the amount of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"force and sign representing the direction)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Num"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Action","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Control Min","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Control Max"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Joint"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unit","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Force applied on the cart"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-3"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slider"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slide"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Force (N)"}]}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"text":"Observation Space","anchor":"Observation-Space","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The state space consists of positional values of different body parts of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pendulum system, followed by the velocities of those individual parts (their derivatives)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"with all the positions ordered before all the velocities."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The observation is a "},{"code":"ndarray","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" with shape "},{"code":"(4,)","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" where the elements correspond to the following:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"rows":[[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Num","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Observation","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Min","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Max"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Name (in corresponding XML file)"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Joint","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Unit","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"0","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"position of the cart along the linear surface","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"slider"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"position (m)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"1"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"vertical angle of the pole on the cart","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Inf","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"angle (rad)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"2"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"linear velocity of the cart","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"slider","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"slide","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"velocity (m\/s)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]],[[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"3"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"angular velocity of the pole on the cart","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"-Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Inf"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"hinge"}],"type":"paragraph"}],[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"anglular velocity (rad\/s)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]]],"type":"table","header":"row"},{"text":"Rewards","anchor":"Rewards","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The goal is to make the inverted pendulum stand upright (within a certain angle limit)"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as long as possible - as such a reward of +1 is awarded for each timestep that"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the pole is upright."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Starting State","anchor":"Starting-State","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All observations start in state"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(0.0, 0.0, 0.0, 0.0) with a uniform noise in the range"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of [-0.01, 0.01] added to the values for stochasticity."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Episode End","anchor":"Episode-End","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The episode ends when any of the following happens:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Truncation: The episode duration reaches 1000 timesteps.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Termination: Any of the state space values is no longer finite."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Termination: The absolutely value of the vertical angle between the pole and the cart is greater than 0.2 radian.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"text":"Arguments","anchor":"Arguments","type":"heading","level":3},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"No additional arguments are currently supported."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":null,"code":["env = gym.make('InvertedPendulum-v4')"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"There is no v3 for InvertedPendulum, unlike the robot environments where a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"v3 and beyond take gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"Version History","anchor":"Version-History","type":"heading","level":3},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v4: all mujoco environments now use the mujoco bindings in mujoco>=2.1.3","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v3: support for gym.make kwargs such as xml_file, ctrl_cost_weight, reset_noise_scale etc. rgb rendering comes from tracking camera (so agent does not run away from screen)"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"v2: All continuous control environments now use mujoco_py >= 1.50","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"v1: max_time_steps raised to 1000 for robot based tasks (including inverted pendulum)","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"v0: Initial versions release (1.0.0)"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"}]}],"sections":[],"references":{"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/Env":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"Env"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/Env","title":"Env","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/gym\/env","abstract":[],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"Env"}]},"doc://org.liuliu.s4nnc/documentation/Gym/InvertedPendulum/model":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.liuliu.s4nnc\/documentation\/Gym\/InvertedPendulum\/model","abstract":[],"fragments":[{"text":"let","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"model","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:6MuJoCo7MjModelV","text":"MjModel"}],"url":"\/documentation\/gym\/invertedpendulum\/model","tit